This paper is about neural networks, which are commonly studied in the machine learning subfield of computer science. The paper specifically focuses on a new approach to defining layers in neural networks, which could be relevant to a number of different subfields within computer science. Based on the abstract and title, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
